    <node id="Gosper's Identity">
      <data key="d0">Gosper's Identity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">An identity for which a new q-analogue has been derived in the study.&lt;SEP&gt;A classical or q-analogue identity used in summation of certain series involving q-shifted factorials.&lt;SEP&gt;A classical identity whose q-analogue is analyzed using the operational simplification provided by the equation.&lt;SEP&gt;A summation formula for which q-analogues are constructed using this equation.&lt;SEP&gt;Gosper's Identity is a mathematical identity for which a new q-analogue is derived in the paper.</data>
